    "created_at": "2014-01-04T04:30:07Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-01-04T04:36:51Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I'm not sure an axis parameter would make sense for a general groupby().apply() method (I do like the idea of consistency with df.groupby though). I believe df.groupby has an axis parameter because DataFrames have two dimensions so axis=0/1 maps to rows/cols. I usually do groupbys with 4-5 levels and depending on what I want I may reduce on the rows or columns or not reduce at all. I like the fact that the apply method on a generic groupby does not assume what you want, and appends results whether you return consistent values, Series, DataFrames, or Panels. \n"
  },
